From bbbd167d12c03b134452f3dc29064809f7af80f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 26 Aug 2025 21:03:48 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:mac80211: allow non-standard HE MCS-12/13

Some AP can possibly try non-standard HE rate and mac80211 warns and drops
packets.

Rate marked as an HE rate but data is invalid: MCS: 12, NSS: 2
WARNING: CPU: 2 PID: 9622 at backports-20250213-6.6.889a0dddfb30f1/net/mac80211/rx.c:5976
ieee80211_rx_list+0x328/0xce8 [mac80211]

Patch-dependency: None

Signed-off-by: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/rx.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/rx.c b/net/mac80211/rx.c
index 5e2d1cc..d0108cb 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/rx.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/rx.c
@@ -6322,7 +6322,7 @@ void ieee80211_rx_list(struct ieee80211_hw *hw, struct ieee80211_sta *pubsta,
 				goto drop;
 			break;
 		case RX_ENC_HE:
-			if (WARN_ONCE(status->rate_idx > 11 ||
+			if (WARN_ONCE(status->rate_idx > 13 ||
 				      !status->nss ||
 				      status->nss > 8,
 				      "Rate marked as an HE rate but data is invalid: MCS: %d, NSS: %d\n",
-- 
2.34.1

